                    <h3>Manage  Database</h3>
                    Add-Edit-Update-Delete information of families and ASHA workers stored in your database.
                    <br>
                    <img src="/assets/how/managedb.png" class="img-polaroid" style="width:75%;">
                    <br>
                    <h4>New ASHA worker</h4>
                    A list of existing already registered ASHA workers under your area is displayed on the right side.<br>Each ASHA worker is identified by a unique ASHA worker ID generated by the system.<br>To make an entry for a new ASHA worker, all you have to do is enter his/her name and mobile number.The unique ID is already created for the new entry.<br>Click ‘Create’ after making the entries. The list of registered ASHA workers on the right gets updated.
                    <br>
                    <img src="/assets/how/asha.png" class="img-polaroid" style="width:75%;">
                    <br>
                    <h4>New Family</h4>
                    Click on ‘New Entry’ to register a new family in your database. A form to be filled will be displayed.
                    <br>
                    <img src="/assets/how/newfamily.png" class="img-polaroid" style="width:75%;">
                    <br>
                    <h4>Update Family</h4>
                    You can update family information such as birth(entry of a new member),etc. Click on the third box on Manage Database page.<br>First of all you need to search the family. To do so provide any one of the four parameters provided on the left side of the screen.<br>More importantly check the checkbox corresponding to that parameter so as to enable it.<br>Click ‘Search’. Down the page all the general details of that family will be displayed in a tabular form. Click ‘Edit’ to edit details of that family.
                    <br>
                    <img src="/assets/how/updatefam.png" class="img-polaroid" style="width:75%;">
                    <br>
                    <h4>Delete Family</h4>
                    You can delete the record of an entire family. Click on the fourth box on Manage Database page.<br>Search for the family you want to delete. Those family details will be displayed down the page. Click on 'delete' on that family
                    <br>
                    <img src="/assets/how/removefam.png" class="img-polaroid" style="width:75%;">
                    <br>
                    After clicking 'delete' it will ask for confirmation (as shown below).
                    <br>
                    <img src="/assets/how/removefamcon.png" class="img-polaroid" style="width:75%;">
                    <br>

